Okay, here is the Go implementation of the brute force method:

```go
func twoSum(nums []int, target int) []int {
    for i := 0; i < len(nums); i++ {
        for j := i + 1; j < len(nums); j++ {
            if nums[i]+nums[j] == target {
                return []int{i, j}
            }
        }
    }
    return nil
}
```

This method has a time complexity of O(nÂ²), suitable for beginners to understand the problem. Would you like to learn about more efficient solutions?
